    "refcode_long": "The Adventist Home, p. 257.1 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "Great care should be exercised to have the surroundings of the mother pleasant and happy. The husband and father is under special responsibility to do all in his power to lighten the burden of the wife and mother. He should bear, as much as possible, the burden of her condition. He should be affable, courteous, kind, and tender, and specially attentive to all her wants. Not half the care is taken of some women while they are bearing children that is taken of animals in the stable.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">6<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"2T 383.3\" data-link=\"120.1664\">Ibid., 2:383</span>.</span></a></sup>",
